p|Croatian Cup Final Four MVP]]: 2000\n* Croatian Cup Final Four Top Scorer: 2000\n* [[50 Greatest EuroLeague Contributors]]: 2008\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{basketballstats|nba=129|bbr=r/radjadi01}}\n* [http://www.euroleague.net/competition/players/showplayer?pcode=AHA#!careerstats Dino Ra\u0111a] at euroleague.net\n* [http://archive.fiba.com/pages/eng/fa/p/lid_38135_cp/1/pid/2648/q/dino%20radja/rpp//_//players.html Dino Ra\u0111a] at fiba.com (archive)\n* [http://www.fibaeurope.com/compID_GSf9wrCdHBkDZZk9UQoqE3.season_2000.roundID_2532.playerID_2648.teamID_1169.html Dino Ra\u0111a] at fibaeurope.com\n* [http://web.legabasket.it/player/?id=RAD-DIN-67 Dino Ra\u0111a] legabasket.it {{in lang|it}}\n\n{{navboxes|list=\n{{FIBA50}}\n{{Euroleague50}}\n{{Euroleague Final Four MVP Award}}\n{{Greek Basket League Finals MVPs}}\n{{Olympiacos B.C.}}\n{{Panathinaikos B.C.}}\n{{KK Split 1988\u201389 Euroleague champions}}\n{{1989 NBA Draft}}\n{{KK Split 1989\u201390 Euroleague champions}}\n{{Pallacanestro Virtus Roma 1991\u201392 FIBA Kora\u0107 Cup champions}}\n{{Yugoslavia Squad EuroBasket 1987}}\n{{Footer 1988 Olympic Silver Medalists Basketball Men}}\n{{Yugoslavia Squad EuroBasket 1989}}\n{{Yugoslavia Squad EuroBasket 1991}}\n{{Footer 1992 Olympic Silver Medalists Basketball Men}}\n{{Croatia Squad EuroBasket 1993}}\n{{Croatia Squad 1994 FIBA World Championship}}\n{{Croatia Squad EuroBasket 1995}}\n{{Croatia Men Basketball Squad 1996 Summer Olympics}}\n{{2018 Basketball HOF}}\n{{Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rada, Dino}}\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:ABA League players]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 1988 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 1992 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 1996 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Boston Celtics draft picks]]\n[[Category:Boston Celtics players]]\n[[Category:Centers (basketball)]]\n[[Category:Croatian expatriate basketball people in Greece]]\n[[Category:Croatian expatriate basketball people in Italy]]\n[[Category:Croatian expatriate basketball people in the United States]]\n[[Category:Croatian men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:FIBA EuroBasket-winning players]]\n[[Category:Greek Basket League players]]\n[[Category:KK Cibona players]]\n[[Category:KK Split players]]\n[[Category:KK Zadar players]]\n[[Category:Lega Basket Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1988 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1992 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame inductees]]\n[[Category:National Basketball Association players from Croatia]]\n[[Category:Olympiacos B.C. players]]\n[[Category:Olympic basketball players of Croatia]]\n[[Category:Olympic basketball players of Yugoslavia]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in basketball]]\n[[Category:Olympic silver medalists for Croatia]]\n[[Category:Olympic silver medalists for Yugoslavia]]\n[[Category:Pallacanestro Virtus Roma players]]\n[[Category:Panathinaikos B.C. players]]\n[[Category:Power forwards (basketball)]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Split, Croatia]]\n[[Category:Yugoslav men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:1994 FIBA World Championship players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{Infobox basketball biography \n| name            = Dino Ra\u0111a\n| image           = DinoRadjaPanathinaikos.jpg \n| width           = \n| caption         = Ra\u0111a with [[Panathinaikos B.C.|Panathinaikos]] in 1998\n| position        = \n| height_ft       = 6\n| height_in       = 11\n| weight_lb       = 225\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1967|04|24|df=y}}\n| birth_place     = [[Split, Croatia|Split]], [[Socialist Republic of Croatia|SR Croatia]], [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|SFR Yugoslavia]]\n| nationality     = Croatian\n| high_school     = \n| college         = \n| draft_year      = 1989\n| draft_round     = 2\n| draft_pic